<name>SUSPENSION &amp; AXLE</name>
<section id="1002H_S000J" variety="S000J">
<name>AXLE</name>
<ttl id="1002H_S000J_7A7ZZ_T004D" variety="T004D">
<name>FRONT AXLE HUB</name>
<para id="RM000000ZZM00IX" category="G" type-id="8000T" name-id="AH02E-02" from="201202">
<name>ON-VEHICLE INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM000000ZZM00IX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000000ZZM00IX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001GO00000">
<ptxt>CHECK FRONT AXLE HUB BEARING</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C136360" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the front wheel.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the front disc brake cylinder (see page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000010KT00SX"/>).</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the front disc.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the axle hub backlash.</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Using a dial indicator, check the backlash near the center of the axle hub.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum backlash</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.05 mm (0.0020 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the backlash is greater than the maximum, replace the bearing.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the axle hub deviation.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C136361" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s3>
<ptxt>Using a dial indicator, check the deviation on the surface of the axle hub.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum deviation</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.05 mm (0.0020 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the deviation is greater than the maximum, replace the bearing.</ptxt>
</s3>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
</pub>
